🟢 Abstract Factory Pattern — Notes
✅ Definition

Abstract Factory provides an interface to create families of related objects without specifying their concrete classes.

🎯 Key Idea

Creates multiple related objects together

Ensures they belong to the same family

Hides object creation logic

🧱 Structure
1️⃣ Abstract Products
interface Button {
    void render();
}

interface TextBox {
    void render();
}
2️⃣ Concrete Products (Family 1)
class DarkButton implements Button {
    public void render() {}
}

class DarkTextBox implements TextBox {
    public void render() {}
}
3️⃣ Concrete Products (Family 2)
class LightButton implements Button {
    public void render() {}
}

class LightTextBox implements TextBox {
    public void render() {}
}
4️⃣ Abstract Factory
interface UIFactory {
    Button createButton();
    TextBox createTextBox();
}
5️⃣ Concrete Factories
class DarkThemeFactory implements UIFactory {
    public Button createButton() {
        return new DarkButton();
    }

    public TextBox createTextBox() {
        return new DarkTextBox();
    }
}
class LightThemeFactory implements UIFactory {
    public Button createButton() {
        return new LightButton();
    }

    public TextBox createTextBox() {
        return new LightTextBox();
    }
}
6️⃣ Client
UIFactory factory = new DarkThemeFactory();

Button b = factory.createButton();
TextBox t = factory.createTextBox();
🔥 What it Ensures

✔ Objects are consistent (same family)
✔ No mixing of incompatible objects
✔ Easy to switch entire system behavior

🧠 When to Use

When objects must be used together

When you need multiple related objects

When system should support multiple configurations/themes

⚠️ Key Insight

Abstract Factory often uses Factory Method internally (each method creates one product).

🟡 Difference: Factory vs Abstract Factory
🎯 Core Difference
Feature	Factory	Abstract Factory
Creates	One object	Family of objects
Focus	Which object	Which family
Methods	Usually 1	Multiple
Example	Payment	UI Theme
Complexity	Simple	Higher
🧠 Example Comparison
Factory
Payment payment = PaymentFactory.getPayment("UPI");

👉 Returns one object

Abstract Factory
UIFactory factory = new DarkThemeFactory();

factory.createButton();
factory.createTextBox();

👉 Returns multiple related objects

⚡ Conceptual Difference
Factory
-------
Select ONE product
(UPI or CARD)


Abstract Factory
----------------
Select FAMILY of products
(Dark Theme → Button + TextBox)
🧠 Interview One-Liner

Factory creates a single object based on input, while Abstract Factory creates a family of related objects ensuring consistency across them.

🔑 Memory Trick
Factory → ONE product

Abstract Factory → MATCHING SET of products
